# Kaivity App Agent Rules

## Core Guidelines
- Write clean, concise, hyper-optimized code. Token conservation is paramount.
- Avoid unnecessary boilerplate, over-engineering, or redundant/obvious comments.
- **No AI Slop:** Be direct and concise. Do not apologize, do not hallucinate polite filler ("I understand", "Here is your code", etc.). Output only technical steps and necessary code.
- **Restricted Files:** NEVER open, modify, or analyze `node_modules` directories or `.env` files under any circumstances.

## Visuals & UI Constraints
- **No Emojis:** NEVER use emojis in code, comments, UI text, or commit messages. This is a strict constraint.
- **Icons Only:** Use proper vector icons for all visual indicators (e.g., Lucide React Native, Expo Vector Icons) instead of text-based emojis.

## Core Theme Architecture
Adhere strictly to the defined constants in `Kaivity/constants/theme.ts`:
- **Brand Colors:** Primary Purple (`#6C63FF`), Light Purple (`#A29BFE`), Dark Purple (`#4834D4`)
- **Accent Colors:** Coral Red (`#FF6B6B`), Success Green (`#2ED573`), Warning Yellow (`#FECA57`)
- **Neutrals:** Light Background (`#F8F9FE`), Surface (`#FFFFFF`), Text Primary (`#1E1E2E`)
- **Category Taxonomy:** Logic (`#6C63FF`), Tracing (`#FF6B6B`), Educational (`#00B894`), Screen-Free (`#FDCB6E`)
- **Dark Mode Support:** BG (`#0F0F1A`), Surface (`#1A1A2E`). Use semantic colors and respect `useColorScheme`.
